Why This Project Uses the MIT License
This repository uses the MIT License because it is one of the most widely adopted open‑source licenses in both academic and industry environments. The MIT License is intentionally simple and permissive, allowing others to view, reuse, modify, and share the code with minimal restrictions. This makes it ideal for educational projects, collaborative learning, and cloud‑based lab work where transparency and accessibility are important.

For this course, the MIT License ensures:

Ease of sharing — classmates, instructors, and reviewers can access the code without legal barriers.

Flexibility — the code can be reused or extended in future coursework or professional projects.

Clarity — the license is short, easy to understand, and avoids complex legal language.

Academic alignment — MIT is a standard choice for student repositories and open‑source learning environments.

Using MIT demonstrates an understanding of open‑source licensing principles while keeping the project accessible and compliant with typical academic expectations.
